00Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"TheJambo/awesome-testing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>Make your life easier</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.baremetalsoft.com/baretail/\">BareTail</a> - Brings the tail linux command to Windows, coloured lines and REGEX search and loads of other features.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-22T10:59:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.csee.umbc.edu/cadip/readings/IR.report.120600.book.pdf\">Information Retrieval: A Survey</a> - Ed Greengrass, 2000. (Comprehensive survey of Conventional Information Retrieval, before Deep Learning era).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-22T05:55:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Network</h2><h3>Honey Pot / Honey Net</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/paralax/awesome-honeypots\">awesome-honeypots</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/paralax/awesome-honeypots\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5.1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5127,\"repo\":\"paralax/awesome-honeypots\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - The canonical awesome honeypot list.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-22T03:34:03.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Network</h2><h3>Monitoring / Logging</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://nodesecurity.io/\">Node Security Platform</a> - Similar feature set to Snyk, but free in most cases, and very cheap for others.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-22T03:29:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Network</h2><h3>IDS / IPS / Host IDS / Host IPS</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ossec.github.io/\">OSSEC</a> - Comprehensive Open Source HIDS. Not for the faint of heart. Takes a bit to get your head around how it works. Performs log analysis, file integrity checking, policy monitoring, rootkit detection, real-time alerting and active response. It runs on most operating systems, including Linux, MacOS, Solaris, HP-UX, AIX and Windows. Plenty of reasonable documentation. Sweet spot is medium to large deployments.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-22T03:29:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Network</h2><h3>IDS / IPS / Host IDS / Host IPS</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://fbb-git.github.io/stealth/\">Stealth</a> - File integrity checker that leaves virtually no sediment. Controller runs from another machine, which makes it hard for an attacker to know that the file system is being checked at defined pseudo random intervals over SSH. Highly recommended for small to medium deployments.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-22T03:05:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"springload/awesome-wagtail","categoryHTML":"<h2>Apps</h2><h3>Widgets</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Frojd/wagtail-geo-widget\">Wagtail-Geo-Widget</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Frojd/wagtail-geo-widget\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">90</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REP